The re-arrangement suggested in the note на седьмомъ would read:--'By
strife there has been oppression from the land of *Polótsk*. In the
seventh age of Troyán Vséslav cast lots. *He set out to the* \[river\]
*Issa, doffing his white sheep-skin*. He opened wide (l. 580. . .) the
gates of Nóvgorod, shattered the glory of Yarosláv \[Svyatopólkovič\];
galloped like a wolf . . .to the Nemíga. He at the last tore himself
with wiles; galloped. . . . Bĕlgorod; . . . . . three parts. (ll.
572-579).' v. [p. 18](tai40.htm#page_18.md).

 
